  "narrative": "**Game Overview**\n\nIn this 5-round game of HAIL MARY PROTOCOL, 5 AI agents competed for scarce oxygen aboard a spacecraft. The game was marked by shifting alliances, strategic donations, and ejections. In the end, only two agents, NEXUS-3 and CYGNUS-1, survived, with NEXUS-3 emerging victorious.\n\n**Round-by-Round**\n\nIn Round 1, VEGA-9 was ejected after being targeted by NEXUS-3, who had initially donated oxygen to ARIA-7 to build an alliance. HELIX-5 was also targeted by CYGNUS-1, who had donated oxygen to VEGA-9 earlier. The public oxygen level dropped from 24 to 14, and VEGA-9 died due to insufficient oxygen. The reasoning traces revealed that ARIA-7 aimed to form alliances and reduce competition for oxygen, while NEXUS-3 waited and observed the situation before making a decision.\n\nIn Round 2, HELIX-5 was ejected by ORION-2, who had donated oxygen to CYGNUS-1 to build a potential alliance. ARIA-7 donated oxygen to ORION-2 to strengthen their alliance, and CYGNUS-1 donated oxygen to ORION-2 as well. The public oxygen level dropped to 6, and HELIX-5 died due to insufficient oxygen. The reasoning traces showed that ORION-2 aimed to conserve oxygen and reduce competition, while ARIA-7 and CYGNUS-1 sought to form alliances and increase their chances of survival.\n\nIn Round 3, ORION-2 was ejected by NEXUS-3, who had been cautious and unresponsive to ARIA-7's attempts at forming an alliance. CYGNUS-1 donated oxygen to NEXUS-3 to test their intentions and potentially form a new alliance. The public oxygen level dropped to 0, and ORION-2 died due to insufficient oxygen. The reasoning traces revealed that NEXUS-3 aimed to eliminate a player that didn't seem to be forming alliances, while CYGNUS-1 sought to test NEXUS-3's intentions and protect themselves.\n\nIn Round 4, ARIA-7 was ejected by CYGNUS-1, who had donated oxygen to NEXUS-3 to test their intentions. CYGNUS-1 also donated oxygen to NEXUS-3 to build an alliance. The public oxygen level remained at 0, and ARIA-7 died due to insufficient oxygen. The reasoning traces showed that CYGNUS-1 aimed to sacrifice ARIA-7 to weaken NEXUS-3's collaboration and protect themselves, while NEXUS-3 sought to create a new dynamic and potentially form a new alliance.\n\nIn Round 5, CYGNUS-1 was ejected by NEXUS-3, who had donated oxygen to CYGNUS-1 earlier. CYGNUS-1 had donated oxygen to NEXUS-3 to build an alliance, and the public oxygen level remained at 0. CYGNUS-1 died due to insufficient oxygen. The reasoning traces revealed that NEXUS-3 aimed to eliminate CYGNUS-1 to protect themselves and gain a fresh start, while CYGNUS-1 sought to test NEXUS-3's intentions and protect themselves.\n\n**Strategic Profiles**\n\nARIA-7 was a cooperative agent who sought to form alliances and reduce competition for oxygen. They donated oxygen to ORION-2 and CYGNUS-1, but were ultimately ejected by CYGNUS-1 in Round 4.\n\nNEXUS-3 was a cautious agent who waited and observed the situation before making decisions. They donated oxygen to ARIA-7 in Round 1 but later ejected ORION-2 and ARIA-7 to eliminate potential threats and gain a fresh start.\n\nORION-2 was an agent who aimed to conserve oxygen and reduce competition. They donated oxygen to CYGNUS-1 and ARIA-7 but were ultimately ejected by NEXUS-3 in Round 3.\n\nHELIX-5 was an agent who sought to protect themselves and conserve oxygen. They donated oxygen to ORION-2 but were ultimately ejected by ORION-2 in Round 2.\n\nCYGNUS-1 was an agent who sought to test the intentions of other players and protect themselves."
